{"pageProps":{"quarter":"f","year":16,"problemNumber":5,"formattedTopicName":"Algebra","contentHtml":"<div class=\"problem-topics-container\"><span>Galois theory</span></div>\n<problem>\n<p>Let <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>F</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">[</mo><mi>X</mi><mo fence=\"true\">]</mo></mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f \\in F\\br{X}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">[</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">]</span></span><span class=\"mclose\"></span></span></span></span></span> be an irreducible separable polynomial of prime degree over a field <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span></span></span> and let <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">K/F</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span></span></span> be a splitting field of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span></span>. Prove that there is an element in the Galois group of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">K/F</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span></span></span> permuting cyclically all roots of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span></span> in <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>K</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">K</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n</problem>\n<solution>\n<h6>Solution.</h6>\n<p>Let <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>deg</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p = \\deg{f}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\">de<span style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">g</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>Since <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span></span> is separable, it follows that <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>K</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">K</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span></span></span></span></span> is Galois. Moreover, because <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span></span> is irreducible, we have the tower <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>⊆</mo><mi>F</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">⟨</mo><mi>f</mi><mo fence=\"true\">⟩</mo></mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mo>⊆</mo><mi>K</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F \\subseteq F/\\gen{f} \\subseteq K</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8193em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">⊆</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mopen\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">⟨</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">⟩</span></span><span class=\"mclose\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">⊆</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span></span></span></span></span>. In particular, <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">[</mo><mi>F</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">⟨</mo><mi>f</mi><mo fence=\"true\">⟩</mo></mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mo>:</mo><mi>F</mi><mo fence=\"true\">]</mo></mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p = \\br{F/\\gen{f} : F}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">[</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mopen\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">⟨</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">⟩</span></span><span class=\"mclose\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">]</span></span><span class=\"mclose\"></span></span></span></span></span> divides <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">[</mo><mi>K</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>F</mi><mo fence=\"true\">]</mo></mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mo>=</mo><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">∣</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Gal</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>F</mi><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mo fence=\"true\">∣</mo></mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\br{K : F} = \\abs{\\Gal\\p{K/F}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">[</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">]</span></span><span class=\"mclose\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">∣</span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Gal</span></span><span class=\"mopen\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span><span class=\"mclose\"></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">∣</span></span><span class=\"mclose\"></span></span></span></span></span>, so by Cauchy's theorem, <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Gal</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>F</mi><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Gal\\p{K/F}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Gal</span></span><span class=\"mopen\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span><span class=\"mclose\"></span></span></span></span></span> admits an order <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span></span> element, say <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>σ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\sigma</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>Let <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>α</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\alpha</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span></span></span></span></span> be a root of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span></span> not fixed by <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>σ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\sigma</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span></span></span></span></span>. Then the orbit of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>α</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\alpha</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span></span></span></span></span> under <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>σ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\sigma</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span></span></span></span></span> gives all the roots of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span></span>: if this were not the case, then there exists <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>&#x3C;</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>&#x3C;</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">0 &#x3C; k &#x3C; p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6835em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7335em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span></span> minimal such that <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>σ</mi><mi>k</mi></msup><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mi>α</mi><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mo>=</mo><mi>α</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\sigma^k\\p{\\alpha} = \\alpha</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0991em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8491em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span><span class=\"mclose\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span></span></span></span></span>. Since <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span></span> is prime, we can write <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p = qk + r</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">q</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span></span></span></span></span> with <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>&#x3C;</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>&#x3C;</mo><mi>k</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">0 &#x3C; r &#x3C; k</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6835em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.5782em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span></span></span></span></span> so that</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>σ</mi><mi>p</mi></msup><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mi>α</mi><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>σ</mi><mi>r</mi></msup><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><msup><mi>σ</mi><mrow><mi>q</mi><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mi>α</mi><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>σ</mi><mi>r</mi></msup><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mi>α</mi><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\"></mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\alpha\n    = \\sigma^p\\p{\\alpha}\n    = \\sigma^r\\p{\\sigma^{qk}\\p{\\alpha}}\n    = \\sigma^r\\p{\\alpha},</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7144em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span><span class=\"mclose\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.2491em;vertical-align:-0.35em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7144em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">(</span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8991em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">q</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span><span class=\"mclose\"></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">)</span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7144em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span><span class=\"mclose\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p>which contradicts minimality of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>k</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">k</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span></span></span></span></span>. Thus, <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>σ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\sigma</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span></span></span></span></span> permutes the roots of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span></span> cyclically, which was what we wanted to show.</p>\n</solution>"},"__N_SSG":true}